name: Simple Hoisin Chicken StirFry Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Place noodles in a large heatproof bowl. Cover with boiling water, then stand for 3 minutes or until softened. Drain. Separate noodles with a fork.

Meanwhile, heat a wok over high heat. Add half the oil, swirling to coat. Stirfry half the chicken for 3 minutes or until just cooked through. Transfer to a bowl. Repeat with remaining oil and chicken. Add 1 tbs sauce to bowl, tossing to coat. Cover.
Add vegetables to wok and stirfry for 3 minutes or until just tender.
Add chicken, noodles and remaining sauce to wok. Stirfry for 3 minutes or until heated through. Divide among bowls and serve.
